{"key":"processedPost-11977395","value":{"id":11977395,"first":11975858,"last":11977481,"when":1265507419,"utime":"02/07/10 03:50 AM","content":"Lots of people use towels, although I feel it's a lot more work than steaming.&nbsp; I wouldn't want to try it with grass seed though.&nbsp; They're awfully small, and besides, it's best not to simmer or soak them other than in the jar itself.&nbsp; Otherwise, you can end up with a big mess. <br /><br />With grass seed, simply use twice as much seed by volume as water or water/coffee, add a pinch of gypsum and give the jar a shake.&nbsp; Let sit for awhile and shake again.&nbsp; Place lid with holes and filter, cover with foil and sterilize.<br />RR","title":"Re: What are some retail stores that sell rye berries?"}}